Thohoyandou
cops have launched a massive search operation for a 3-year-old boy who went
missing on Monday. Mukhwathi
Ndiwakhonadzeo was allegedly playing with friends in an open field when he disappeared.  Randzilani said a massive search was conducted in the bushes, abandoned houses,
open pits and a near-by river but the search was unsuccessful. He said the search operation has resumed under heavy rains and will proceed
until the child is located. The child is dark in complexion and was wearing only a navy blue track pants
when he disappeared. Randzilani urged anyone with information that can assist in locating the
missing toddler to urgently contact Sergeant Makhavhu on 0764404336 or Crime Stop
on